The evidence with the title 'The truths and tales of Cuban healthcare | US & Canada | Al Jazeera ' says Jun 18, 2012  ... The state - run system has been praised , but many specialists now fear they are falling behind international standards. ... Despite its scarce resources , Cuba has one of the world 's lowest infant mortality rates - just slightly lower than that of the US . Life expectancy is 77.5 years, one of the world's highest. 
